#%Module1.0

module-whatis           "XPMEM is a Linux kernel module that enables a process to map the memory of another process into its virtual address space."
module-url              "https://github.com/hpc/xpmem"
module-license          "$PREFIX/share/doc/xpmem/COPYING"
module-maintainer       "Marc Caubet Serrabou <marc.caubet@psi.ch>"

module-help             "
This is an experimental version of XPMEM based on a version provided by Cray
and uploaded to https://code.google.com/p/xpmem. This version supports any
Linux kernel 3.12 and newer (tested up to 5.8.x). Keep in mind there may be bugs and
this version may cause kernel panics, code crashes, eat your cat, etc.

XPMEM is a Linux kernel module that enables a process to map the
memory of another process into its virtual address space.
"
